2️⃣ On fine hair, levels 7 and up I use the least amount recommended. For coarse hair & or on darker levels I only 5-7 grams.  I don’t like my lightened hair to be overly neutralized I still like it a bit raw before I tone.

If I were to start my hairstyling career all over again this is what I would tell my younger self …

⚡️ Realize success is a journey, not a destination. If I were to start over, I’d embrace every challenge as an opportunity to evolve. Your passion and dedication are the keys – the rest will follow.

⚡️ Create boundaries early on and not let clients,friends or family bully you into discounted services.  Learn to respect your career & in return people will respect your craft.

⚡️ Always level up your skills and stay educated through mentorship, courses and practicing your craft so that you’re continuously growing.

⚡️Stay true to yourself.  Don’t feel you need to always be constantly posting & sharing.  Share what feels aligned for you and your business not just bc others have done it or “you have to”.

⚡️Make time for yourself.  This job is going to take a lot mentally & physically out of you! So don’t loose YOU in the journey!

I Shampoo after I tone, HBY?

Why I shampoo after toning you may ask? 

🦋Residue Removal: Shampooing after toning helps remove any leftover toner residue, ensuring a clean and balanced hair surface.

❤️Product Layering: Shampooing prevents toner buildup, allowing subsequent hair care products, like conditioners or treatments, to be more effective.

🔥Balanced pH: Shampooing helps restore the natural pH balance of the hair after the toning process, promoting overall hair health.

🌺Enhanced Styling: Clean hair allows for better styling results, as products adhere more evenly to the hair shaft.

Reasons why I don’t use purple shampoo or conditioner before I tone platinum hair;

🔥Color Interference: Purple shampoo is designed to neutralize yellow or brassy tones in blonde or light-colored hair. Using it before toning can interfere with the toner’s intended color correction, as purple shampoo may deposit its own color pigments.

🔥Unpredictable Results: The combination of purple shampoo and toner might lead to unpredictable color outcomes, as these products may counteract or interact in unexpected ways.

🔥Uneven Color Absorption: Toning agents may not penetrate the hair evenly if there’s a residue from purple shampoo, affecting the uniformity of the color correction process.

💦Barrier Effect: Conditioner can create a barrier on the hair shaft, potentially hindering the toner’s ability to penetrate and interact with the hair cuticle effectively.

💦Uneven Color Absorption: The presence of conditioner may result in uneven absorption of the toner, leading to inconsistent color results.

💦Diminished Toning Efficacy: Conditioner, especially those with silicones, may coat the hair, making it less receptive to the toning agents and reducing the efficacy of the toning process.
